South African Committee Increases Corn Crop Estimate 0.5% on Higher Yields

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-04-20T13:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/south-african-committee-increases-corn-crop-estimate-0-5-on-higher-yields.html
South Africa ’s Crop Estimates
Committee increased its forecast for this season’s corn crop by
0.5 percent to 10.88 million metric tons on expectations of
improved yields.  The yellow corn crop forecast was raised 1.1 percent to
4.62 million tons while the estimate for white corn was
unchanged at 6.26 million tons, Marda Scheepers, a spokeswoman
for the committee, said by phone today from  Pretoria .  The median forecast of 13 traders surveyed by Bloomberg
News was for the estimate to remain unchanged from last month’s
10.83 million tons.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at   ajordan11@bloomberg.net  